Morphology. Female. General features —Idiosoma elongated oval; frontal platelets shorter than shoulder platelets (shoulder/frontal platelets L ratio 1.2–1.4 ); frontal margin medially convexly rounded, between anterolaterally pointed apodemes (
Fig. 22 C
); Cx-I with rounded tips, Cxgl– 4 located far distal, nearly at tips of Cx- I; gnathosomal bay deep, U-shaped; genital field pentagonal; suture line of Cx-IV distinct, originating from lateral edge of genital field and extending far beyond posterior margin of the genital field (
Fig. 22 B
); excretory pore and Vgl- 2 posterior to the line of primary sclerotization, Vgl- 2 slightly posterior to excretory pore; gnathosoma with protruding rostrum, pointed in lateral view (
Fig. 22 G
); chelicera with a long, needle-like claw; palps compact and stout, P- 4 ventral margin almost straight without ventral setae (
Figs. 22 D–E
); I-L with I-L- 6 L/H ratio 1.9 , basally narrowed, distally thickened (
Fig. 22 F
).
